I"<p><b>Ingredients</b></p>
<ul>
  <li>500g Arroz redondo</li>
  <li>8 Mushrooms (champignon)</li>
  <li>1 Onion</li>
  <li>1L Vegetable Broth</li>
  <li>2 Tsp Nutritional Yeast</li>
  <li>8 Dried Tomatoes</li>
  <li>1 Tsp Salt</li>
  <li>1 Tsp Black Pepper</li>
  <li>125ml White Wine</li>
  <li>250g Broccoli</li>
</ul>

<p><b>Instructions</b></p>
<ol>
  <li>Slice mushrooms into slices and fry with oil, salt and black pepper. Put aside.</li>
  <li>Cut onion into cubes and fry (5 mins).</li>
  <li>Add rice and fry until transparent.</li>
  <li>Add white wine and cook until the wine volatilises.</li>
  <li>Add broccoli and vegetable broth in steps of 125ml. Stir regularly.</li>
  <li>After 15 to 20 minutes remove rice and add oil, nutritional yeast and mushrooms.</li>
</ol>
